<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>DBZ: Legendary Super Warriors — Guide</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Press+Start+2P&family=Share+Tech+Mono&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #0a0c10;
    --surface: #111318;
    --surface2: #181c24;
    --border: #2a3040;
    --accent: #f4a800;
    --accent2: #ff4444;
    --accent3: #4fc3f7;
    --text: #d8dde8;
    --text-dim: #7a8599;
    --glow: 0 0 12px rgba(244,168,0,0.3);
  }

  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  body {
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: 'Share Tech Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  /* Scanline overlay */
  body::before {
    content: '';
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    background: repeating-linear-gradient(
      0deg,
      transparent,
      transparent 2px,
      rgba(0,0,0,0.08) 2px,
      rgba(0,0,0,0.08) 4px
    );
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 1000;
  }

  .shell {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 16px 60px;
  }

  /* Header */
  header {
    padding: 40px 0 24px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    position: relative;
  }

  header::after {
    content: '';
    display: block;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--accent3);
    margin-top: 4px;
    opacity: 0.3;
  }

  .game-label {
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    color: var(--accent3);
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', monospace;
    font-size: clamp(13px, 3vw, 20px);
    color: var(--accent);
    text-shadow: var(--glow);
    line-height: 1.5;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 12px;
    margin-top: 10px;
  }

  /* Nav tabs */
  nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    background: var(--bg);
    padding: 10px 0;
    z-index: 100;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  nav a {
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', monospace;
    font-size: 8px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 6px 10px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    transition: all 0.15s;
    background: var(--surface);
  }

  nav a:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--surface2);
    box-shadow: var(--glow);
  }

  /* Sections */
  section {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
    scroll-margin-top: 70px;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-shadow: var(--glow);
    padding-bottom: 8px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }

  h3 {
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    color: var(--accent3);
    margin: 20px 0 10px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }

  p { margin-bottom: 12px; color: var(--text); }

  /* Tables */
  .tbl-wrap { overflow-x: auto; margin-bottom: 16px; }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  th {
    background: var(--surface2);
    color: var(--accent);
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', monospace;
    font-size: 8px;
    padding: 8px 12px;
    text-align: left;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }

  td {
    padding: 7px 12px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    vertical-align: top;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  tr:nth-child(even) td { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); }
  tr:hover td { background: rgba(244,168,0,0.04); }

  /* Boss cards */
  .boss-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; }

  .boss-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 14px 16px;
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .boss-card:hover { border-left-color: var(--accent3); }

  .boss-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .boss-name {
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .diff {
    font-size: 11px;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border: 1px solid;
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', monospace;
    font-size: 7px;
  }

  .diff-easy    { color: #4caf50; border-color: #4caf50; }
  .diff-normal  { color: var(--accent3); border-color: var(--accent3); }
  .diff-hard    { color: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent); }
  .diff-vhard   { color: var(--accent2); border-color: var(--accent2); }

  .boss-tip { color: var(--text); font-size: 13px; }

  /* Unlock table difficulty labels */
  code {
    background: var(--surface2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    font-family: 'Share Tech Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--accent3);
  }

  /* Card columns */
  .two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    h1 { font-size: 11px; }
  }

  .card-list {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 12px 16px;
  }

  .card-list h4 {
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', monospace;
    font-size: 8px;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .card-list ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3px 10px;
  }

  .card-list li::before {
    content: '▸ ';
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .card-list li { font-size: 12px; }

  /* Info box */
  .info-box {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent3);
    padding: 12px 16px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .info-box p { margin: 0; }

  /* CC table */
  .cc-table { background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); }

  /* Walkthrough steps */
  .wt-step {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 14px 16px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .step-num {
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', monospace;
    font-size: 7px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  /* All-cards grid */
  .cards-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(160px, 1fr));
    gap: 4px;
  }

  .card-entry {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 5px 8px;
    font-size: 12px;
  }

  /* Inline warning */
  .warn {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', monospace;
    font-size: 7px;
    padding: 2px 6px;
    background: var(--surface2);
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-right: 4px;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }

  footer {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 20px 0;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 11px;
    margin-top: 40px;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="shell">

  <header>
    <div class="game-label">Game Boy Advance · RPG</div>
    <h1>Dragon Ball Z:<br>Legendary Super Warriors</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Cleaned & reorganized guide — original content by Crotanks / RPGClassics</p>
  </header>

  <nav>
    <a href="#basics">Basics</a>
    <a href="#controls">Controls</a>
    <a href="#battle">Battle System</a>
    <a href="#walkthrough">Walkthrough</a>
    <a href="#bosses">Boss Guide</a>
    <a href="#characters">Characters</a>
    <a href="#cards">Cards</a>
    <a href="#secrets">Secrets</a>
    <a href="#codes">Codes</a>
  </nav>

  <!-- BASICS -->
  <section id="basics">
    <h2>Basics</h2>

    <h3>In-Game Menu</h3>
    <div class="tbl-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>Status</code></td><td>View character stats. When you level up, distribute 5 bonus points here to one stat.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>Deck</code></td><td>Add or remove joint cards. Max 20 cards per deck. Once all 20 are drawn in battle, no more can be drawn, but the battle continues.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>Team</code></td><td>Choose your team if the battle allows it. After clearing the game once, any character can be used.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>List</code></td><td>View all collected cards.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>Save</code></td><td>Save your game.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>Exit</code></td><td>Returns to the map, or starts battle if you're pre-battle.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3>Leveling Up</h3>
    <p>Maximum level is 5. You gain levels by fighting. On levelup, you receive 5 points to allocate to one stat.</p>
    <div class="tbl-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Stat</th><th>Effect</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>HP</td><td>Increases survivability in battle.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Strength</td><td>Increases damage from damage cards and command cards.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Ki</td><td>Increases damage from beam attacks.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Speed</td><td>Improves accuracy and avoidance. Also determines who attacks first.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CONTROLS -->
  <section id="controls">
    <h2>Controls</h2>
    <div class="tbl-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Button</th><th>Action</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>D-Pad</td><td>Navigate menus and move on the map.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>A</td><td>Confirm, interact, advance text.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>B</td><td>Cancel / return to previous screen.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Start</td><td>Start game; view card details in System Screen.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Select</td><td>Not used.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BATTLE SYSTEM -->
  <section id="battle">
    <h2>Battle System</h2>

    <h3>Overview</h3>
    <p>Battles are card-based. Each turn you choose from the command bar at the bottom of the screen. HP of both fighters is shown in opposite corners — reduce the enemy to zero to win.</p>
    <p>If a battle allows 2 fighters, use <strong>C (Select Character)</strong> to swap them. If one dies, the other is brought out automatically.</p>

    <h3>Commands</h3>
    <div class="tbl-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Command</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>B — Basic</code></td><td><strong>Attacking:</strong> Gather power, or perform a 3-stage attack (4-stage if powered up).<br><strong>Defending:</strong> Move or defend. Defending reduces incoming damage; moving changes your position (see Position table).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>J — Joint</code></td><td>Use support and ability cards from your deck. May or may not cost CC depending on the card.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>L — Limited</code></td><td>Cards usable repeatedly if you have enough CC. Characters can hold up to 3 Limited cards (Androids 19 &amp; 20 can only hold 2). To assign limited cards: Menu → Team → select character → "Limit".</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>C — Character</code></td><td>Switch to your other fighter if one is available.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3>Position Effects</h3>
    <div class="tbl-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Position</th><th>Vulnerable To</th><th>Front</th><th>Back</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>In the Air</td><td>Beam Attacks</td><td>Attack ↑, Defense ↓</td><td>Attack ↓, Defense ↑</td></tr>
          <tr><td>On the Ground</td><td>Damage Attacks</td><td>Attack ↑, Defense ↓</td><td>Attack ↓, Defense ↑</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p>Basic attacks do <strong>not</strong> cost CC.</p>

    <h3>Card Cost (CC)</h3>
    <p>CC is shown in the lower-right corner of the battle screen as <code>CC: /13</code>. You need CC to use Limited cards. Ways to gain CC:</p>
    <div class="tbl-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Trigger</th><th>CC Gained</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>You are the attacker</td><td>+3</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Each successful command in a Command Card (3-stage = 3 commands)</td><td>+1 per command</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Your HP drops substantially</td><td>+2</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Hit in the air by Beam, or on the ground by Damage (amount varies by position)</td><td>Variable</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3>Enemy AI Pattern</h3>
    <div class="info-box">
      <p>Regular attack → Gather power → 5-stage attack → Beam or Damage attack → Repeat. Enemies rarely use energy cards unless powered up — so don't waste yours either unless necessary.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Post-Battle</h3>
    <p>After each battle, you choose <strong>1 card</strong> from 3 options.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- WALKTHROUGH -->
  <section id="walkthrough">
    <h2>Walkthrough</h2>

    <div class="wt-step">
      <div class="step-num">SAIYAN SAGA</div>
      <p>The game starts after Raditz's defeat. Piccolo is training Gohan. Talk to Piccolo, find the jars (answer the battle system question to get a card), return to Piccolo and repeat until he asks you to pick a deck. <span class="warn">Recommended: Beam Deck.</span></p>
      <p>Fight Piccolo → Pick a card → Watch scene.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="wt-step">
      <p>After the Saiyans arrive and Piccolo dies saving Gohan: fight Nappa as Gohan → Pick a card.</p>
      <p>Goku arrives and leads Vegeta away. <strong>Before the Vegeta fight</strong>, equip Goku's limit with Super Kamehameha and Kaioken.</p>
      <p>Fight Vegeta (Goku) → Pick card → scene.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="wt-step">
      <p>After Vegeta beats Goku: Go to the nearest rock formation and press A to get <strong>Yajirobe's sword</strong>. Talk to Krillin → say yes. Talk to Yajirobe. Fight Vegeta again (Gohan/Krillin) → pick card.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="wt-step">
      <div class="step-num">NAMEK SAGA</div>
      <p>On the map, go left to the Namekian village. Find the house reachable only through the row of trees → press A → get the <strong>Dende card</strong>. Go to the island and press A by the rightmost tree to dig up a Dragon Ball. A Namekian accuses you; dodge left.</p>
      <p>Fight Guldo → fight Recoome → fight Jeice &amp; Burter.</p>
      <p>After Burter/Jeice: go to the top-left corner of the map and press A at the space pod for a card. Follow the dirt path north → collect Dragon Balls → talk to Krillin.</p>
      <p>Fight Ginyu (Goku's body) &amp; Jeice → fight Freeza.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="wt-step">
      <p>After first Freeza fight: Freeza nearly kills Piccolo and kills Krillin, pushing Goku to go Super Saiyan. Switch to Gohan, find Bulma in the NW of the map. Talk to her → say no → go to the pile of rocks and press A for a card → go back to Bulma → say yes. Fight Freeza again (as SSJ Goku).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="wt-step">
      <div class="step-num">ANDROID SAGA</div>
      <p>After Namek, talk to Piccolo and search for him 5 times (find his ki). Get Gohan's Dunk Shot from Piccolo, another card from Chichi, and the 5 Stage Attack from Goku. Fight Goku (training battle).</p>
      <p>After scene: Talk to Krillin, Vegeta, and Piccolo. Find Tien in the northern cliffs (press A). Fight Android 20 → fight Cell (lose once to unlock Piccolo-God, then win).</p>
      <p>After Cell escapes: In the chamber building, find the note behind the building and follow its instructions to get <strong>Kaio, Trunks' Sword, and Solid Shot</strong>. Talk to Goku for something strange. Fight Android 16 &amp; 18.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="wt-step">
      <div class="step-num">CELL GAMES</div>
      <p>Cell Games begin. Fight Cell as Goku → then as SSJ2 Gohan (Cell Jr. battle) → Gohan vs Cell main fight → <span class="warn">Use Vegeta for the final Cell battle</span> to unlock the extra Trunks story.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="wt-step">
      <div class="step-num">TRUNKS' STORY (unlockable)</div>
      <p>Trunks returns to his future. Talk to NPCs on the map for character unlock hints. Fight Androids 17 &amp; 18 as Super Trunks (use the card from Bulma). Fight Cell.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="wt-step">
      <div class="step-num">BUU SAGA</div>
      <p>6 years later. Gohan is in high school. On the map: Piccolo is in the NW corner, Videl in SE. Talk to Goten and fight him (easy). Then fight Young Trunks at the Martial Arts Tournament (Goten's perspective).</p>
      <p>After the tournament: Talk to everyone on the Babidi map to advance. Fight Majin Vegeta as SSJ2 Goku.</p>
      <p>On the next map: Press A on Piccolo and Krillin → find Videl → talk to Trunks. Fight Fat Buu.</p>
      <p>Goten &amp; Trunks master fusion. Gohan gets powered up by Old Kai. Fight Buu (normal) → Buu (absorb) → Buu (Gotenks absorbed) → Buu as Vegito → Evil Buu (final boss). <span class="warn">Recommended: have SSJ3 Goku unlocked for the final fight.</span></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BOSS GUIDE -->
  <section id="bosses">
    <h2>Boss Guide</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:16px;color:var(--text-dim);font-size:12px;">Walkthrough bosses only — bosses that appear exclusively in the walkthrough are listed with full tips here. Second-round unlock bosses follow the same general strategy: build CC, power up, use your best attack.</p>

    <div class="boss-list">

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Piccolo</span>
          <span class="diff diff-easy">EASY</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">You attack first. Use a 3-stage attack for CC. If he gathers power, do the same. Use Foresight before his 4/5-stage attack if you have it. Try a 4-stage attack or Masenko. When he uses Special Beam Cannon, use an avoid card or move Gohan to the bottom-left corner. Repeat.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Nappa</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Same strategy as Piccolo. Pummel with 3- and 4-stage attacks. If he hasn't powered up by his 4th or 5th turn, have Endurance ready. If he does power up, use the Piccolo strategy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Vegeta (Goku)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-hard">HARD (first time)</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Before the fight, set Goku's limits to Super Kamehameha and Kaioken. Attack normally with 3- and 4-stage attacks. When Vegeta powers up, have Goku power up too, use Kaioken on defense, then Super Kamehameha on offense. Watch out for Galick-Ho at this stage — it hurts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Vegeta (Gohan/Krillin)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Same as the Goku fight, but without Goku's support. Same strategy applies.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Guldo</span>
          <span class="diff diff-easy">EASY</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Choose Krillin (to get him to at least level 2) or Gohan. Standard strategy throughout.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Recoome</span>
          <span class="diff diff-hard">ALMOST HARD</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Wail with 3- and 4-stage attacks. After significant damage, he'll use Eraser Gun for heavy damage — be ready for it.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Jeice &amp; Burter</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">First 2v2 battle. Put Gohan front, Goku back. Use Dende when either is near 1/4 HP. Once Jeice is down, Burter switches to Mach Attack — have Shockwave ready. When possible, have Goku power up → Kaioken → Spirit Bomb.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Ginyu (Goku's body) &amp; Jeice</span>
          <span class="diff diff-easy">EASY</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Ginyu will use Super Kamehameha — be careful. Standard tactics. Swap to Krillin if Gohan gets low; use Misty Ki Wave with Krillin. Jeice may or may not use Crasher Ball. Swap back to Gohan if Krillin gets low and finish Jeice.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Freeza (1st fight)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-hard">ALMOST HARD</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Freeza loves Ground Wave and Super Dash Elbow after powering up. Build CC to ~65–70, then use Kaioken + Spirit Bomb for massive damage.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Freeza (2nd fight — SSJ Goku)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-hard">ALMOST HARD</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Same as before but no Kaioken. Spirit Bomb still works. Build CC with normal tactics, then spam Super Kamehameha and Spirit Bombs.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Goku (training)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-easy">EASY</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Pushover. But he will use Spirit Bomb when he fires Ki attacks, which drains HP fast. Build CC and use Masenkos or Dunk Shot.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Android 19</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">May or may not absorb Ki attacks (doesn't do it often). Has an HP drain attack. Build CC, power up, Spirit Bomb.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Android 20</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Same as 19, but uses Super E-Ball as his special. Normal strategy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Cell (first encounter)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Have Piccolo-God if possible. If not, lose once → continue → beat him. Watch for Special Beam Cannon and Super Kamehameha.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Android 17</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">SEMI-NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Piccolo-God makes this much easier. Won't absorb energy but uses Crazy Rush and Super E-Ball. Normal tactics; use Special Beam Cannon when available.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Android 16 &amp; 18</span>
          <span class="diff diff-hard">ALMOST HARD</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">16 favors Rocket Punch; 18 uses a variety. Have Goku-SS assist if possible.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Cell (Cell Games — vs Goku)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Same as first encounter but may use Cell Combo. He mainly uses Special Beam Cannon.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Cell Jr. (Gohan SSJ2)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-easy">VERY EASY</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Same Cell strategy. Easy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Cell (vs Gohan)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Gohan can now use Super Kamehameha. Set it up and use the same Cell strategy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Cell (vs Vegeta — FINAL)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Same strategy. <span class="warn">Use Vegeta here to unlock the extra Trunks story.</span></p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Androids 17 &amp; 18 (Trunks' story)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Use Super Trunks only. Include the card received from Bulma in your deck.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Cell (Trunks' story)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Same strategies used when fighting him as Piccolo.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Trunks (kids tournament)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Stronger than Goten. Uses Burning Attack and Flash Punch. Have Goten's Kamekameha. Guard specials while using normal strategy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Majin Vegeta</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">You have SSJ2 Goku. Vegeta now has Final Flash and Big Bang Attack. Build CC and power without dealing too much damage. If he flies up: Spirit Bomb.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Fat Buu</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Watch out for Super E-Ball and Potbelly Attack. Normal strategy. Final Flash or Big Bang Attack helps.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Young Trunks (Time Chamber)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Uses Rising Kick and Burning Attack. Normal tactics.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Buu (vs Gotenks SSJ3)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Watch for Super E-Ball. Normal tactics.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Buu (vs Mystic Gohan)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Same as above. Use Super Kamehameha if Gohan has it.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Buu (Gotenks + Piccolo absorbed)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">This Buu counters Super Kamehameha with Breathe. Avoid it; use any other cards while sticking to normal strategy to learn his moves.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Buu (vs Vegito)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-normal">NORMAL</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip">Equip Vegito with Super Kamehameha, Teleportation, and Big Bang Attack. Should be straightforward.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="boss-card">
        <div class="boss-header">
          <span class="boss-name">Evil Buu (Final Boss)</span>
          <span class="diff diff-vhard">NORMAL+</span>
        </div>
        <p class="boss-tip"><span class="warn">Have SSJ3 Goku unlocked — it makes this significantly easier.</span> Standard strategy by this point.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

